{"lemma":"حام","slug":"حام","root":"ح.م.#","root_slug":"ح-م-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-م-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حام","root":"حمي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9231","n9627"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%85"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"extremely hot","examples":[{"text":"وُجُوهٌ يَوْمَئِذٍ خَاشِعَةٌ\n عَامِلَةٌ نَاصِبَةٌ\n تَصْلَى نَارًا حَامِيَةً\n تُسْقَى مِنْ عَيْنٍ آنِيَةٍ\n لَيْسَ لَهُمْ طَعَامٌ إِلَّا مِنْ ضَرِيعٍ\n لَا يُسْمِنُ وَلَا يُغْنِي مِنْ جُوعٍ","english":"[Some] faces, that Day, will be humbled,\nWorking [hard] and exhausted.\nThey will [enter to] burn in an intensely hot Fire.\nThey will be given drink from a boiling spring.\nFor them there will be no food except from a poisonous, thorny plant\nWhich neither nourishes nor avails against hunger."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"vehement, ardent, fiery, heated, violent, forceful (of an emotion such as anger)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"steamy (erotic)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of حَمَى (ḥamā, “to protect”)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a protector","examples":[{"text":"حُمَاةَ الْحِمَى يَا حُمَاةَ الْحِمَى\n هَلُمُّوا هَلُمُّوا لِمَجْدِ الزَّمَنْ","english":"O defenders of the Homeland\n rally around to the glory of our time!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a stallion-camel freed from work","examples":[{"text":"مَا جَعَلَ اللّٰهُ مِن بَحِيرَةٍ وَلَا سَائِبَةٍ وَلَا وَصِيلَةٍ وَلَا حَامٍ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hover, to revolve around"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ḥām, the son of Nūḥ and the brother of Yāfiṯ and Sām."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare حَمِيم (ḥamīm).\n\nFrom the active participle of حَمَى (ḥamā, “to protect”).\nThe sense ‘stallion-camel freed from work’ has been explained as coming from the image of a stallion-camel protecting its back: \"a stallion-camel that has prohibited, or interdicted, his back [to be used for bearing a rider or any burden]\".\n\nFrom Biblical Hebrew חָם (ḥām)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9231","headword_ar":"حَامٍ","root":"HmY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaY","text_ar":"حَمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". And hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stallion-camel that has prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interdicted, his back"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to be used for bearing a rider or any burden]; ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zahorahu","text_ar":"ظَهْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaY","text_ar":"حَمَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; Fr, S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is not ridden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor shorn of any of his fur;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is left at liberty, not made any use of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor debarred from pasturage"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, Mgh, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor from water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) he is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that has long continued with a people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose offspring's offspring has conceived:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has covered a certain number of times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten times:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) it is mentioned in the Kur [v. 102]. (S, Mgh. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHiyrapN","text_ar":"بَحِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaAmiY","text_ar":"الحَامِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also an appellation applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaHomiY~u","text_ar":"المَحْمِىُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) in the Tekmileh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHAmY","text_ar":"الحامى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHomY","text_ar":"المُحْمى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHomiY","text_ar":"المُحْمِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in a copy of the K]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN HaAmiY AlHaqiyqapi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ حَامِى الحَقِيقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the protector,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defender, of that which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those whom, it is necessary for him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incumbent on him, to protect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defend"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmiY Al*~imaAri","text_ar":"حَامِى الذِّمَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*mr","text_ar":"ذمر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmiY AlHumay~aA","text_ar":"حَامِى الحُمَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained in the next preceding paragraph]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumaApN","text_ar":"حُمَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmiyapN","text_ar":"حَامِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) this last word signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, protecting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defending, their companions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"themselves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and also a man who is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a protector,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defender, of his companions"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in war:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strenuous protector and defender"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a party; for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is to give intensiveness to the signification: (Mgh:) and you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa EalaY HaAmiyapi Alqawomi","text_ar":"هُوَ عَلَى حَامِيَةِ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the last of those who protect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defend, the party in their going away"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in their state of defeat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemently hot."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiydapN HaAmiyapN","text_ar":"حَدِيدَةٌ حَامِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of iron vehemently hot by means of fire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidoru Alqawomi","text_ar":"قِدْرُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmiyapN tafuwru","text_ar":"حَامِيَةٌ تَفُورُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people's cooking-pot is hot, boiling:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people are mighty, strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"invincible, and vehemently impetuous in valour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","S","Mgh","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9627","headword_ar":"حَامَ","root":"Hwm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hawola AlmaA='i","text_ar":"حَوْلَ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَلَى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHuwmu","text_ar":"يَحُومُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawamaAnN","text_ar":"حَوَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawomN","text_ar":"حَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) said of a bird, or flying thing, (S, Msb, K,) &c., (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hovered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"round about the water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of thirst,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"round about the thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmato","text_ar":"حَامَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of camels. (K, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano HaAma Hawola","text_ar":"مَنْ حَامَ حَوْلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHimaY yuw$ika A^ano yaqaEa fiyhi","text_ar":"الحِمَى يُوشِكَ اَنْ يَقَعَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who approaches acts of disobedience is near to falling therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yaHuwmu Hawola","text_ar":"هُوَ يَحُومُ حَوْلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaDK lahu","text_ar":"غَرَضٍ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hovers about an object of aim,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desire, that he has"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAm fulaAnN EalaY","text_ar":"حام فُلَانٌ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amori","text_ar":"الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawomN","text_ar":"حَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiyaAmN","text_ar":"حِيَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw^uwmN","text_ar":"حُوُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) the second with kesr [to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", but written in the CK with fet-h], (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one desired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought, the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAm EalaY qaraAbatihi","text_ar":"حام عَلَى قَرَابَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He affected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclined towards, his relations, like one going round about the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}